elements.description: Category

C is an internal category in D if given two objects
C0 and C1, respectively the objects and morphisms
of C, if the following diagrams commute.
Map objects to their identity morphism
Internal Definition

Form the pullbacks of objects and morphisms
and lift to the pullback assembly of composable
pairs of identities and morphisms.

Form the pullback of composable morphisms
where the first's codomain equals the second's
domain.

From the above pullback there must be a morphism
giving the composition of the two morphisms.

The domain of the composite must be the domain
of the first morphism.

The codomain of the composite must be the codomain
of the latter morphism.

The codomain of the identity of an object is
that object itself.

The domain of the identity of an object is
that object itself.
